sarah and i have been planning to do some backpacking in sunol since we read about it on the [redwood hikes site](https://www.redwoodhikes.com/EastBay/SunolCG.html). all the info on there is really top notch so we trusted the author about it being one of the best backpacking campsites in the bay area. the only thing they were wrong about is how busy it would be. during our whole stay we were the only folks there. lucky us!

ultimately sarah put it best:

>I experienced so much awe on this trip it’s hard to put into language. We hiked to the highest campsite, Sky Camp, which was probably the hardest I’ve ever done. The last 3 miles felt so steep. What I didn't expecting was just how beautiful the view we were hiking up to was. The photos do not do it justice. You’re so high up airplanes look their actual size, and you’re making eye contact with vultures.

we saw lots of animals in fact. vultures, a few cows, a snake, so many squirrels, lizards, and hawks. apparently the ohlone wilderness is also host to eagles but we unfortunately didn't catch any. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/exhaustion.png)

emboldened by the ranger at the visitor center we opted to take the steeper and rockier mccorkle trail to get to the site. it did kick our asses but i think the views of the hills were worth it.

![image](assets/images/sunol/panoramic.png)

after the unexpectedly super hard hike up to the site, we sat down on our foam mats to snack on some dried fruit and rehydrate. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/mats.png)

we pitched the tent facing the sky and rolled up the outer layer so we could look out. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/tent.png)

before too long we were cooking up some dinner. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/dinnermaking.png)

dehydrated beans and rice with avocado and organic fritos. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/dinny.png)

and finally the sunset.

![image](assets/images/sunol/sunset.png)

looking back on our little campsite

![image](assets/images/sunol/campsite.png)

in the morning we got a chance to bust out some bags of ground coffee to steep and enjoy with some stroopwaffles looking out on the hills. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/coffeemorning.png)

obviously we had to bust out some cute outfits for the hike home. 

![image](assets/images/sunol/sarahday2fit.png)

![image](assets/images/sunol/alexday2fit.png)





